Sentencas: The electrical properties of a series of perovskite-related cuprates have been investigated at elevated temperatures with a view to using these types of materials as solid oxide fuel cell cathodes.

In this study, the compositions La6.4-xSr1.6+xCu8-xFex O20+/-delta s where 0less than or equal toxless than or equal to2 are investigated as a preliminary study to investigate the feasibility of developing these materials as cathodes.
The materials reported here have a peak conductivity at 300 K of 1.46 x 10(3)
S cm(-1) for the undoped material dropping to 5.0 x 10(2) S cm(-1) at 1043 K.
This is well above the minimum requirement for a cathode material and suggests that further investigation is warranted.
